ed by <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/the-brutalist"><em>The Brutalist</em></a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/wicked"><em>Wicked</em></a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/conclave-review-pope-ralph-fiennes-stanley-tucci-3815998"><em>Conclave</em></a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/a-complete-unknown"><em>A Complete Unknown</em></a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/anora"><em>Anora</em></a> .</p><p> You can follow all the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/oscars-2025-winners-full-list-3842814">rolling coverage of the ceremony right here</a> , with a winners list being updated as the evening progresses.</p><p> This year&#39;s Oscars have done away with <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/the-2025-oscars-will-not-include-performances-for-best-original-song-category-3831285">performances for Best Original Song</a> , while the show honoured Los Angeles after the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/entertainment-world-reacts-to-heart-wrenching-los-angeles-wildfires-3827340">recent wildfires</a> with a nod by host Conan O&#39;Brien before later inviting many firefighters on stage.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/best-documentary-oscar-winner-no-other-land-praised-for-moving-speech-on-palestine-3842824">Best Documentary Oscar winner &#39;No Other Land&#39; praised for “moving” speech on Palestine</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
